				<div class="message">Actually I don't. And it's one of the reasons why I don't.<br />
<br />
I'm debating it, but it doesn't sound like my kind of game. That's not a dig on the games mind you. I've just hit that point where being an adult smacks you in the face so hard that you start to get picky about how you waste your time.<br />
<br />
Being the extrovert that I am - I really don't care too much about exploration in single player games. MMORPGs break this for me because I can involve other people in the exploration and that makes it more fun for me.<br />
<br />
If you're the type of person that loves to quietly explore for the sake of exploring, this game is awesome for it. If you're exploring to get some kind of meaning out of the act - less so.</div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>I find that I really have no patience for games that require loads of dickering to get to faster paced, more attention intensive parts anymore. They are just boring to me now; I think I am just growing out of interest in video games for the most part anymore. I would rather play or participate in something that is face to face like poker or dancing or hashing out plans, schemes, and tooling anymore I guess as they have a lower time incurred to get to the good parts and keep me hyped. Surprisingly I prefer games that are more oriented towards women anymore also as the few that do exist are much more like a visual novel than going from node to node with minimal direction, guessing what the trigger is for the next event is and a more  difficult to follow plot as it is sparsely revealed over the journey.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
