				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Dark Souls: My (new) All-Time Favorite Game.
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1829961">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				<div class="bbcode_postedby">
					<img src="images/misc/quote_icon.png" alt="Quote" /> Originally Posted by <strong>QuelianSpyralshot</strong>
					<a href="showthread.php?s=ef035035ca80ac30c4a1f3dbbb883709&amp;p=1829808#post1829808" rel="nofollow"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/buttons/viewpost-right.png" alt="View Post" /></a>
				</div>
				<div class="message">I've just hit that point where being an adult smacks you in the face so hard that you start to get picky about how you waste your time.</div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>I felt exactly the way you did a few years ago.  But now, I try and find time to enjoy both.  Sometimes I like exploring IRL-- new cities, new people, new outdoor challenges, etc., and sometimes I enjoy playing a game.  So, I try to choose the games I play very carefully, and won't continue playing something that isn't worth it.  In this case, I was drawn to Dark Souls after playing and being disappointed with Legend of Zelda: Ocarina of Time (there's a thread on the forum about it).<br />
<br />
<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				I'm debating it, but it doesn't sound like my kind of game. That's not a dig on the games mind you.
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>Specifically you claimed it was repetitive.  I find it hard to believe your experience actually supports that claim.  I have played it for 300 hours or so at this point, and while I have definitely found repetitive portions of the game, most of them are optional except where you are stuck on a boss you can't beat and have to keep running back to the fog gate for each attempt.  The optional repetitive parts are if you want to farm souls(xp+gp) and equipment-upgrade materials.<br />
<br />
<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				If you're the type of person that loves to quietly explore for the sake of exploring, this game is awesome for it. If you're exploring to get some kind of meaning out of the act - less so.
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>What does &quot;get some kind of meaning out of it&quot; even mean?
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
