			<div class="postrow">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Dark Souls: My (new) All-Time Favorite Game.
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1829967">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				<div class="bbcode_postedby">
					<img src="images/misc/quote_icon.png" alt="Quote" /> Originally Posted by <strong>QuelianSpyralshot</strong>
					<a href="showthread.php?s=ef035035ca80ac30c4a1f3dbbb883709&amp;p=1829841#post1829841" rel="nofollow"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/buttons/viewpost-right.png" alt="View Post" /></a>
				</div>
				<div class="message">Directed at me or Goladus? I don't hate dark souls. I just sort of had a moment at 10 hours in that was like &quot;Ok, gameplay isn't going to change for the next 200 hours and I really don't care enough about the story to proceed.&quot; It just pushed past my patience.</div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>Do you happen to remember what elements of the gameplay you hoped would change?<br />
<br />
The game's gameplay is fine really. The enemies are all solid. There's nothing WRONG with the game. The problem is my real life is actually more interesting than the game at the moment so I'm focusing on that. We could do a lot <b>worse</b> than dark souls. <br />
<br />
<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				I just think if they'd bothered to put some better NPC interaction in it'd have gripped me harder.
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>NPC interaction in Dark Souls is definitely not its strong point, but I am quite happy with the amount of it they chose to include.  Specifically: not much.  NPCs are there to support and enhance the gameplay, not the other way around.  I particularly like the way most NPC faces are hidden, so I'm not distracted by an uncanny valley of expressions and body language.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="cleardiv"></div>
		</div>
	</div>
		<div class="postfoot">
